      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CRACKA TINNY (7) scored at Gloucester Park two runs ago before having his colours lowered when sixth at his latest appearance over 2100m at the Central Wheatbelt, beaten 21 metres. Will enjoy a pretty soft run from this draw, with the sprint lane to play a big role. Meets a similar line up and he can figure in the finish. PACIFIC EAGLE (3) turned in an uncharacteristically poor run last start when 24 metres away in sixth over 2190m at this track. Form prior to that had been solid. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a similar line up and he is capable of a much better performance. IDEAL WHITBY (4) has been thereabouts of late and is a great chance to break through. Good effort last time out when he finished fifth at the Central Wheatbelt over 1730m. GOODONYA MATE (1) is worth some thought after his last-start sixth over 1730m at the Central Wheatbelt on May 3.",
